reviews.review_text: nice I only listened to a little bit of this, but the sound quality is great, the vocals are clear, and definatly worth the download

Great memories This was my first real show (Bakersfield in 78 doesn't count, sat too far away and smoked too much!)

I arrived late, wanting to see what my friends were all so jazzed about.  I drove up to the amphitheater hearing this crazy slide guitar on Little Red Rooster.  As I walked up, I saw that they had speakers set up outside.  Bought a ticket for $10 and ventured in.  Spotted my friends in front of the soundboard and made my way over there through all the tapers ("Look out!  Hey!") as Jerry was singing "He blacked my eye and kicked my dog!".

I was home.
Outstanding AUD Audience recordings don't get any better, and this is a REALLY good show. Don't even need the "for the 80's" disclaimer. Maybe no "best of evers", but real solid from start to finish.

Fantastic I found this show through a "Looks like rain" top performances list. It is actually all that but a lot more. This is probably one of the best Cassidys I've heard too, and I'm just getting started. Jerry's guitar sounds great on here... and Brent!!!!!!
4.5 stars
